    "short_description": {
        "value": "GeoKR is a geographical knowledge-driven representation learning and network pre-training method for remote sensing images. It leverages global land cover products (GlobeLand30) and geographical location as supervision for representation learning, using a mean-teacher framework to mitigate supervision noise. Pretraining is performed on the Levir-KR dataset (1,431,950 Gaofen satellite images), and the model is evaluated on scene classification, semantic segmentation, object detection, and cloud/snow detection tasks.",
